1. U poslednjem napadu, bilo je mnogo *žrtava*. (In the last attack, there were many *victims*.)
2. Kada je poplava pogodila grad, mnogi su ostali bez svojih *žrtava*. (When the flood hit the city, many lost their *belongings*.)
3. Životinje u šumi su ponekad *žrtve* lovaca. (Animals in the forest are sometimes *prey* of hunters.)
4. *Žrtava* nasilja u porodici često ćute i ne traže pomoć. (Victims of domestic violence often remain silent and do not seek help.)
5. Svake godine se održava memorijal u čast *žrtava* Drugog svetskog rata. (Every year, a memorial is held in honor of the *victims* of World War II.)
6. Pripadnici vojske i policije se rizikuju svoje živote da bi zaštitili *žrtve* terorističkih napada. (Soldiers and police officers risk their lives to protect *victims* of terrorist attacks.)
7. Porodice poginulih *žrtava* avionske nesreće još uvek se bore da saznaju istinu o tome šta se dogodilo. (Families of the deceased *victims* of the plane crash are still fighting to find out the truth about what happened.)
8. Najviše *žrtava* koronavirusa je zabeleženo u starijim populacijama. (The highest number of *victims* of coronavirus was recorded among the elderly population.)
9. Danas se obeležava Dan sećanja na sve *žrtve* rata i ratnih sukoba. (Today is marked as the Day of Remembrance for all *victims* of war and armed conflicts.)
10. Kada je izbio požar, stanovnici su bili primorani da napuste svoje domove i sa sobom su poneli samo najneophodnije stvari, ostavljajući sve ostalo kao *žrtve* vatre. (When the fire broke out, residents were forced to leave their homes and only took the most necessary things with them, leaving everything else as *victims* of the fire.)